  "prompt": "What are the disadvantages of not using Facebook? What are the advantages?",
  "response": "Disadvantages of not using Facebook:\n\n1. Limited social connectivity\n2. Missed event invitations\n3. Reduced networking opportunities\n4. Less access to group information\n5. Difficulty staying updated with friends and family\n6. Potentially missing professional networking chances\n7. Limited exposure to news and current events\n8. Less ability to quickly share photos and life updates\n\nAdvantages of not using Facebook:\n\n1. Increased personal privacy\n2. Reduced digital distractions\n3. More time for real-world interactions\n4. Lower risk of data breaches\n5. Less exposure to negative news and online conflicts\n6. Reduced social comparison and potential mental health issues\n7. Protection from potential online harassment\n8. Less targeted advertising\n9. Improved mental well-being\n10. More focus on direct, meaningful communications\n11. Decreased risk of social media addiction\n12. Protection from potential employer/professional screening\n13. Lower chance of personal information being misused\n14. More control over personal information\n15. Less screen time\n\nThe impact varies based on individual circumstances, social networks, and personal preferences.",
